task.summary: Prototype ready. Scarcely tested, but already it looks like the Dispatcher manages thread shortage (and multiple queues) badly. See TODOs.
Fixed bug in Dispatcher (bad eviction algorithm) Fixed bug in DownloadableFilePart (close of HttpEntity InputStream caused deadlocks)

Refactor: split tasks (File and Part) and workers (moved to the comms package). Now it should be mockable.
Rewritten Dispatcher: now all tasks live inside one PriorityBlockingQueue, and the number of threads is managed on the thread pool level.
Cleanup. Refactor. Javadoc. TODO: task management in dispatcher, UT.
Support non-resumable tasks and correct restart of them.
